symbols.name: sap.ui.unified
symbols.description: Unified controls intended for both, mobile and desktop scenarios

symbols.name: sap.ui.unified.Calendar
symbols.description: Basic Calendar. This calendar is used for DatePickers

properties.name: intervalSelection
properties.description: If set, interval selection is allowed

properties.name: singleSelection
properties.description: If set, only a single date or interval, if intervalSelection is enabled, can be selected

properties.name: months
properties.description: Determines the number of months displayed. As of version 1.50, the duplicated dates are not displayed if there are multiple months. Note: On phones, only one month is displayed.

properties.name: firstDayOfWeek
properties.description: If set, the first day of the displayed week is this day. Valid values are 0 to 6. If not a valid value is set, the default of the used locale is used.

properties.name: nonWorkingDays
properties.description: If set, the provided weekdays are displayed as non-working days. Valid values inside the array are 0 to 6. If not set, the weekend defined in the locale settings is displayed as non-working days. Note: Keep in mind that this property sets only weekly-recurring days as non-working. If you need specific dates or dates ranges, such as national holidays, use the specialDates aggregation to set them. Both the non-working days (from property) and dates (from aggregation) are visualized the same.

properties.name: primaryCalendarType
properties.description: If set, the calendar type is used for display. If not set, the calendar type of the global configuration is used.

properties.name: secondaryCalendarType
properties.description: If set, the days are also displayed in this calendar type If not set, the dates are only displayed in the primary calendar type

properties.name: width
properties.description: Width of Calendar Note: There is a theme depending minimum width, so the calendar can not be set smaller.

properties.name: minDate
properties.description: Minimum date that can be shown and selected in the Calendar. This must be a JavaScript date object. Note: if the date is inside of a month the complete month is displayed, but dates outside the valid range can not be selected. Note: If the minDate is set to be after the maxDate, the maxDate is set to the end of the month of the minDate.

properties.name: maxDate
properties.description: Maximum date that can be shown and selected in the Calendar. This must be a JavaScript date object. Note: if the date is inside of a month the complete month is displayed, but dates outside the valid range can not be selected. Note: If the maxDate is set to be before the minDate, the minDate is set to the begin of the month of the maxDate.

properties.name: showWeekNumbers
properties.description: Determines whether the week numbers in the months are displayed. Note: For Islamic calendars, the week numbers are not displayed regardless of what is set to this property.

aggregations.name: selectedDates
aggregations.description: Dates or date ranges for selected dates. To set a single date (instead of a range), set only the startDate property of the {@link sap.ui.unified.DateRange} class.

aggregations.name: specialDates
aggregations.description: Dates or date ranges with type, to visualize special days in the Calendar. If one day is assigned to more than one Type, only the first one will be used. To set a single date (instead of a range), set only the startDate property of the {@link sap.ui.unified.DateRange} class. Note: Keep in mind that the NonWorking type is for marking specific dates or date ranges as non-working, where if you need a weekly-reccuring non-working days (weekend), you should use the nonWorkingDays property. Both the non-working days (from property) and dates (from aggregation) are visualized the same.

aggregations.name: disabledDates
aggregations.description: Dates or date ranges for disabled dates. To set a single date (instead of a range), set only the startDate property of the {@link sap.ui.unified.DateRange} class.

aggregations.name: header
aggregations.description: Hidden, for internal use only.

associations.name: ariaLabelledBy
associations.description: Association to controls / ids which label this control (see WAI-ARIA attribute aria-labelledby).

associations.name: legend
associations.description: Association to the CalendarLegend explaining the colors of the specialDates. Note The legend does not have to be rendered but must exist, and all required types must be assigned.

symbols.name: sap.ui.unified.calendar.Month
symbols.description: renders a month with ItemNavigation This is used inside the calendar. Not for stand alone usage If used inside the calendar the properties and aggregation are directly taken from the parent (To not duplicate and sync DateRanges and so on...)

properties.name: date
properties.description: A date as JavaScript Date object. The month including this date is rendered and this date is focused initially (if no other focus is set).

properties.name: intervalSelection
properties.description: If set, interval selection is allowed

properties.name: singleSelection
properties.description: If set, only a single date or interval, if intervalSelection is enabled, can be selected

properties.name: showHeader
properties.description: If set, a header with the month name is shown

properties.name: firstDayOfWeek
properties.description: If set, the first day of the displayed week is this day. Valid values are 0 to 6. If not a valid value is set, the default of the used locale is used.

properties.name: nonWorkingDays
properties.description: If set, the provided weekdays are displayed as non-working days. Valid values inside the array are 0 to 6. If not set, the weekend defined in the locale settings is displayed as non-working days.

properties.name: primaryCalendarType
properties.description: If set, the calendar type is used for display. If not set, the calendar type of the global configuration is used.

properties.name: secondaryCalendarType
properties.description: If set, the days are also displayed in this calendar type If not set, the dates are only displayed in the primary calendar type

properties.name: width
properties.description: Width of Month

properties.name: showWeekNumbers
properties.description: Determines whether the week numbers in the months are displayed. Note: For Islamic calendars, the week numbers are not displayed regardless of what is set to this property.

aggregations.name: selectedDates
aggregations.description: Date Ranges for selected dates of the DatePicker

aggregations.name: specialDates
aggregations.description: DateRange with type to visualize special days in the Calendar. Note: If one day is assigned to more than one DateTypeRange, only the first one will be used. The only exception is when one of the types is NonWorking, then you can have both NonWorking and the other type. For example, you can have NonWorking + Type01 but you can't have Type01 + Type02.

aggregations.name: disabledDates
aggregations.description: Date Ranges for disabled dates

associations.name: ariaLabelledBy
associations.description: Association to controls / ids which label this control (see WAI-ARIA attribute aria-labelledby).

associations.name: legend
associations.description: Association to the CalendarLegend explaining the colors of the specialDates. Note The legend does not have to be rendered but must exist, and all required types must be assigned.

events.name: select
events.description: Date selection changed

events.name: focus
events.description: Date focus changed

otherMonth.name: otherMonth
otherMonth.description: focused date is in an other month that the displayed one

restoreOldDate.name: restoreOldDate
restoreOldDate.description: focused date is set to the same as before (date in other month clicked)

events.name: weekNumberSelect
events.description: Fired when a week number selection is changed. By default, choosing the week number will select the corresponding week. If the week has already been selected, choosing the week number will deselect it. The default behavior can be prevented using the preventDefault method. Note: Works for Gregorian calendars only and when intervalSelection is set to true.

weekDays.name: weekDays
weekDays.description: The days of the corresponding week that are selected or deselected. Note: Will be set to null if that week is being deselected.

parameters.name: sId
parameters.description: id for the new control, generated automatically if no id is given

parameters.name: mSettings
parameters.description: initial settings for the new control

symbols.name: sap.ui.unified.calendar.MonthsRow
symbols.description:
Renders a row of months using ItemNavigation. There is no paging or navigation outside the rendered area implemented. This is done inside the CalendarMonthInterval. If used inside the CalendarMonthInterval the properties and aggregation are directly taken from the parent (to not duplicate and synchronize DateRanges and so on...).

The MontsRow works with JavaScript Date objects, but only the month and the year are used to display and interact. As representation for a month, the 1st of the month will always be returned in the API.

properties.name: date
properties.description: A date as JavaScript Date object. The month including this date is rendered and this date is focused initially (if no other focus is set). If the date property is not in the range startDate + months in the rendering phase, it is set to the startDate. So after setting the startDate the date should be set to be in the visible range.

properties.name: startDate
properties.description: Start date, as JavaScript Date object, of the row. The month of this date is the first month of the displayed row.

properties.name: months
properties.description: Number of months displayed

properties.name: intervalSelection
properties.description: If set, interval selection is allowed

properties.name: singleSelection
properties.description: If set, only a single month or interval, if intervalSelection is enabled, can be selected Note: Selection of multiple intervals is not supported in the current version.

properties.name: showHeader
properties.description: If set, a header with the years is shown to visualize what month belongs to what year.

aggregations.name: selectedDates
aggregations.description: Date ranges for selected dates. If singleSelection is set, only the first entry is used. Note: Even if only one day is selected, the whole corresponding month is selected.

aggregations.name: specialDates
aggregations.description: Date ranges with type to visualize special months in the row. If one day is assigned to more than one type, only the first one will be used. Note: Even if only one day is set as a special day, the whole corresponding month is displayed in this way.

associations.name: ariaLabelledBy
associations.description: Association to controls / IDs which label this control (see WAI-ARIA attribute aria-labelledby).

associations.name: legend
associations.description: Association to the CalendarLegend explaining the colors of the specialDates. Note The legend does not have to be rendered but must exist, and all required types must be assigned.

symbols.name: sap.ui.unified.calendar.TimesRow
symbols.description:
Renders a row of time items using ItemNavigation. There is no paging or navigation outside the rendered area implemented. This is done inside the CalendarTimeInterval. If used inside the CalendarTimeInterval the properties and aggregation are directly taken from the parent (to not duplicate and synchronize DateRanges and so on...).

The TimesRow works with JavaScript Date objects.

properties.name: date
properties.description: A date as JavaScript Date object. The month including this date is rendered and this date is focused initially (if no other focus is set). If the date property is not in the range startDate + items in the rendering phase, it is set to the startDate. So after setting the startDate the date should be set to be in the visible range.

properties.name: startDate
properties.description: Start date, as JavaScript Date object, of the row.

properties.name: items
properties.description: Number of time items displayed

properties.name: intervalMinutes
properties.description: Size of on time interval in minutes, default is 60 minutes. Note: the start of the interval calculation is always startDat at 00:00. An interval longer than 720 minutes is not allowed. Please use the DatesRow instead. A day must be divisible by this interval size. One interval must not include more than one day.

properties.name: intervalSelection
properties.description: If set, interval selection is allowed

properties.name: singleSelection
properties.description: If set, only a single month or interval, if intervalSelection is enabled, can be selected Note: Selection of multiple intervals is not supported in the current version.

properties.name: showHeader
properties.description: If set, a header with the years is shown to visualize what month belongs to what year.

aggregations.name: selectedDates
aggregations.description: Date ranges for selected dates. If singleSelection is set, only the first entry is used.

aggregations.name: specialDates
aggregations.description: Date ranges with type to visualize special item in the row. If one day is assigned to more than one type, only the first one will be used.

associations.name: ariaLabelledBy
associations.description: Association to controls / IDs which label this control (see WAI-ARIA attribute aria-labelledby).

associations.name: legend
associations.description: Association to the CalendarLegend explaining the colors of the specialDates. Note The legend does not have to be rendered but must exist, and all required types must be assigned.

symbols.name: sap.ui.unified.CalendarMonthInterval
symbols.description: Calendar with granularity of months displayed in one line. Note: JavaScript Date objects are used to set and return the months, mark them as selected or as a special type. But the date part of the Date object is not used. If a Date object is returned the date will be set to the 1st of the corresponding month.

properties.name: width
properties.description: Width of the CalendarMonthInterval. The width of the single months depends on this width.

properties.name: startDate
properties.description: Start date of the Interval as JavaScript Date object. The month of this Date will be the first month in the displayed row.

properties.name: intervalSelection
properties.description: If set, interval selection is allowed

properties.name: singleSelection
properties.description: If set, only a single date or interval, if intervalSelection is enabled, can be selected Note: Selection of multiple intervals is not supported in the current version.

properties.name: months
properties.description: Number of months displayed Note: On phones, the maximum number of months displayed in the row is always 6.

properties.name: pickerPopup
properties.description: If set, the yearPicker opens on a popup

properties.name: minDate
properties.description: Minimum date that can be shown and selected in the Calendar. This must be a JavaScript date object. Note: If the minDate is set to be after the maxDate, the maxDate is set to the end of the month of the minDate.

properties.name: maxDate
properties.description: Maximum date that can be shown and selected in the Calendar. This must be a JavaScript date object. Note: If the maxDate is set to be before the minDate, the minDate is set to the begin of the month of the maxDate.

aggregations.name: selectedDates
aggregations.description: Date ranges for selected dates of the CalendarMonthInterval. If singleSelection is set, only the first entry is used. Note: Even if only one day is selected, the whole corresponding month is selected.

aggregations.name: specialDates
aggregations.description: Date ranges with type to visualize special months in the CalendarMonthInterval. If one day is assigned to more than one type, only the first one will be used. Note: Even if only one day is set as a special day, the whole corresponding month is displayed in this way.

aggregations.name: header
aggregations.description: Hidden, for internal use only.

associations.name: ariaLabelledBy
associations.description: Association to controls / IDs which label this control (see WAI-ARIA attribute aria-labelledby).

associations.name: legend
associations.description: Association to the CalendarLegend explaining the colors of the specialDates. Note The legend does not have to be rendered but must exist, and all required types must be assigned.

symbols.name: sap.ui.unified.CalendarRow
symbols.description: A calendar row with a header and appointments. The Appointments will be placed in the defined interval.

properties.name: startDate
properties.description: Start date, as JavaScript Date object, of the row. As default, the current date is used.

properties.name: intervals
properties.description: Number of displayed intervals. The size of the intervals is defined with intervalType

properties.name: intervalType
properties.description: Type of the intervals of the row. The default is one hour.

properties.name: showSubIntervals
properties.description: If set, subintervals are shown. If the interval type is Hour, quarter hours are shown. If the interval type is Day, hours are shown. If the interval type is Month, days are shown.

properties.name: showIntervalHeaders
properties.description: If set, interval headers are shown like specified in showEmptyIntervalHeaders. If not set, no interval headers are shown even if intervalHeaders are assigned.

properties.name: showEmptyIntervalHeaders
properties.description: If set, interval headers are shown even if no intervalHeaders are assigned to the visible time frame. If not set, no interval headers are shown if no intervalHeaders are assigned. Note: This property is only used if showIntervalHeaders is set to true.

properties.name: nonWorkingDays
properties.description: If set, the provided weekdays are displayed as non-working days. Valid values inside the array are 0 to 6. (Other values will just be ignored.) If not set, the weekend defined in the locale settings is displayed as non-working days. Note: The non working days are only visualized if intervalType is set to day.

properties.name: nonWorkingHours
properties.description: If set, the provided hours are displayed as non-working hours. Valid values inside the array are 0 to 23. (Other values will just be ignored.) Note: The non working hours are only visualized if intervalType is set to hour.

properties.name: width
properties.description: Width of the row

properties.name: height
properties.description: Height of the row

properties.name: checkResize
properties.description: If set, the CalendarRow checks for resize by itself. If a lot of CalendarRow controls are used in one container control (like PlanningCalendar). the resize checks should be done only by this container control. Then the container control should call handleResize of the CalendarRow if a resize happens.

properties.name: updateCurrentTime
properties.description: If set the CalendarRow triggers a periodic update to visualize the current time. If a lot of CalendarRow controls are used in one container control (like PlanningCalendar) the periodic update should be triggered only by this container control. Then the container control should call updateCurrentTimeVisualization of the CalendarRow to update the visualization.

properties.name: groupAppointmentsMode
properties.description: Defines the mode in which the overlapping appointments are displayed. Note: This property takes effect, only if the intervalType of the current calendar view is set to sap.ui.unified.CalendarIntervalType.Month. On phone devices this property is ignored, and the default value is applied.

properties.name: appointmentsReducedHeight
properties.description: If set the appointments without text (only title) are rendered with a smaller height. Note: On phone devices this property is ignored, appointments are always rendered in full height to allow touching.

properties.name: appointmentsVisualization
properties.description: Defines the visualization of the CalendarAppoinment Note: The real visualization depends on the used theme.

aggregations.name: appointments
aggregations.description: Appointments to be displayed in the row. Appointments outside the visible time frame are not rendered. Note: For performance reasons, only appointments in the visible time range or nearby should be assigned.

aggregations.name: intervalHeaders
aggregations.description: Appointments to be displayed in the top of the intervals. The intervalHeaders are used to visualize public holidays and similar things. Appointments outside the visible time frame are not rendered. The intervalHeaders always fill whole intervals. If they are shorter than one interval, they are not displayed. Note: For performance reasons, only appointments in the visible time range or nearby should be assigned.

associations.name: ariaLabelledBy
associations.description: Association to controls / IDs which label this control (see WAI-ARIA attribute aria-labelledby). Note These labels are also assigned to the appointments.

associations.name: legend
associations.description: Association to the CalendarLegend explaining the colors of the Appointments. Note The legend does not have to be rendered but must exist, and all required types must be assigned.

methods.description: Sets a new value for property {@link #getNonWorkingDays nonWorkingDays}. If set, the provided weekdays are displayed as non-working days. Valid values inside the array are 0 to 6. (Other values will just be ignored.) If not set, the weekend defined in the locale settings is displayed as non-working days. Note: The non working days are only visualized if intervalType is set to day. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored.

returnValue.description: Reference to this in order to allow method chaining

Valid values inside the array are 0 to 23. (Other values will just be ignored.) Note: The non working hours are only visualized if intervalType is set to hour. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored.

returnValue.description: Reference to this in order to allow method chaining

parameters.name: bShowEmptyIntervalHeaders
parameters.description: New value for property showEmptyIntervalHeaders

methods.description: Sets a new value for property {@link #getShowEmptyIntervalHeaders showEmptyIntervalHeaders}. If set, interval headers are shown even if no intervalHeaders are assigned to the visible time frame. If not set, no interval headers are shown if no intervalHeaders are assigned. Note: This property is only used if showIntervalHeaders is set to true. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored. Default value is true.

returnValue.description: Reference to this in order to allow method chaining

If not set, no interval headers are shown even if intervalHeaders are assigned. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored. Default value is true.

methods.description: Sets a new value for property {@link #getShowSubIntervals showSubIntervals}. If set, subintervals are shown. If the interval type is Hour, quarter hours are shown. If the interval type is Day, hours are shown. If the interval type is Month, days are shown. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored. Default value is false.

methods.description: Sets a new value for property {@link #getUpdateCurrentTime updateCurrentTime}. If set the CalendarRow triggers a periodic update to visualize the current time. If a lot of CalendarRow controls are used in one container control (like PlanningCalendar) the periodic update should be triggered only by this container control. Then the container control should call updateCurrentTimeVisualization of the CalendarRow to update the visualization. methods.name: updateCurrentTimeVisualization

returnValue.description: this to allow method chaining

methods.description: If the current time is in the visible output of the CalendarRow, the indicator for the current time must be positioned. For this, each CalendarRow can trigger a timer. But if multiple CalendarRows are used in one container (e.G. PlanningCalendar), it is better if the container triggers the interval once and then calls this function of each CalendarRow.

symbols.name: sap.ui.unified.CalendarTimeInterval
symbols.description: Calendar with granularity of time items displayed in one line.

properties.name: width
properties.description: Width of the CalendarTimeInterval. The width of the single months depends on this width.

properties.name: startDate
properties.description: Start date of the Interval as JavaScript Date object. The time interval corresponding to this Date and items and intervalMinutes will be the first time in the displayed row.

properties.name: intervalSelection
properties.description: If set, interval selection is allowed

properties.name: singleSelection
properties.description: If set, only a single date or interval, if intervalSelection is enabled, can be selected Note: Selection of multiple intervals is not supported in the current version.

properties.name: items
properties.description: Number of time items displayed. Default is 12. Note: On phones, the maximum number of items displayed in the row is always 6.

properties.name: intervalMinutes
properties.description: Size of on time interval in minutes, default is 60 minutes. Note: the start of the interval calculation is always on the corresponding date at 00:00. An interval longer than 720 minutes is not allowed. Please use the CalendarDateInterval instead. A day must be divisible by this interval size. One interval must not include more than one day.

properties.name: pickerPopup
properties.description: If set, the day-, month- and yearPicker opens on a popup

properties.name: minDate
properties.description: Minimum date that can be shown and selected in the Calendar. This must be a JavaScript date object. Note: If the minDate is set to be after the maxDate, the maxDate is set to the end of the month of the minDate.

properties.name: maxDate
properties.description: Maximum date that can be shown and selected in the Calendar. This must be a JavaScript date object. Note: If the maxDate is set to be before the minDate, the minDate is set to the begin of the month of the maxDate.

aggregations.name: selectedDates
aggregations.description: Date ranges for selected items of the CalendarTimeInterval. If singleSelection is set, only the first entry is used.

aggregations.name: specialDates
aggregations.description: Date ranges with type to visualize special items in the CalendarTimeInterval. If one interval is assigned to more than one type, only the first one will be used.

aggregations.name: header
aggregations.description: Hidden, for internal use only.

associations.description: Association to controls / IDs which label this control (see WAI-ARIA attribute aria-labelledby).

associations.description: Association to the CalendarLegend explaining the colors of the specialDates. Note The legend does not have to be rendered but must exist, and all required types must be assigned.

symbols.name: sap.ui.unified.ColorPicker
symbols.description: Enables the user to select a color. The color can be defined using HEX, RGB, or HSV values or a CSS color name. Note: Keep in mind that this control needs either sap.m or sap.ui.commons library to be loaded in order to work as it depends on controls available in one or the other library.

properties.name: colorString
properties.description:
Determines the input parameter that can be a string of type HEX, RGB, HSV, or a CSS color name:
  • HEX - #FFFFFF
  • RGB - rgb(255,255,255)
  • HSV - hsv(360,100,100)
  • CSS - red
Note: The output parameter is an RGB string of the current color.

properties.name: mode
properties.description: Determines the color mode of the ColorPicker.

properties.name: displayMode
properties.description: Determines the display mode of the ColorPicker among three types - Default, Large and Simplified

symbols.name: sap.ui.unified.Currency
symbols.description:
A text view which displays currency values and aligns them at the decimal point.

Overview

The currency control consists of an amount, which is formatted automatically according to the users locale (using delimiter symbols for the decimal point and thousand separators) and to the currency set for this specific number (number of decimal places). The currency is expressed as a three-letter code.

Usage

When to use
  • To display amounts with different currencies in a vertical layout, such as in a table, list, or form, and it is important that the user is able to compare the amounts.
When not to use
  • To display amounts with the same currency in a table. Use the {@link sap.m.ObjectNumber} instead.
  • to display a number with a unit of measurement that is not a currency. Use the {@link sap.m.ObjectNumber} instead.
  • To display an amount in a structure other than a list, table, or form.

Responsive behavior

The control supports amounts smaller than 100 trillion, which still fit on a phone screen in portrait mode. For larger amounts, the unit of measurement wraps to the next line, which makes it difficult to compare the amounts.

properties.name: value
properties.description: Determines the currency value.

properties.name: stringValue
properties.description: Determines the currency value as a string. String value is useful if you want to store really big values. If there are more than 21 digits before the decimal point or if the number starts with 0. followed by more than five zeros, it is represented in exponential form. In these cases use the stringValue property to keep the number in decimal format. Note: If set, it will take precedence over the value property.

properties.name: currency
properties.description: Determines the displayed currency code (ISO 4217). Note: If a * character is set instead of currency code, only the character itself will be rendered, ignoring the value property.

properties.name: maxPrecision
properties.description: Defines the space that is available for the precision of the various currencies.

properties.name: useSymbol
properties.description: Displays the currency symbol instead of the ISO currency code.

symbols.name: sap.ui.unified.FileUploader
symbols.description: The framework generates an input field and a button with text "Browse ...". The API supports features such as on change uploads (the upload starts immediately after a file has been selected), file uploads with explicit calls, adjustable control sizes, text display after uploads, or tooltips containing complete file paths.

properties.name: value
properties.description: Value of the path for file upload.

properties.name: enabled
properties.description: Disabled controls have different colors, depending on customer settings.

properties.name: uploadUrl
properties.description: Used when URL address is on a remote server.

properties.name: name
properties.description: Unique control name for identification on the server side after sending data to the server.

properties.name: width
properties.description: Specifies the displayed control width.

properties.name: uploadOnChange
properties.description: If set to "true", the upload immediately starts after file selection. With the default setting, the upload needs to be explicitly triggered.

properties.name: additionalData
properties.description: Additional data that is sent to the back end service. Data will be transmitted as value of a hidden input where the name is derived from the name property with suffix -data.

properties.name: sameFilenameAllowed
properties.description: If the FileUploader is configured to upload the file directly after the file is selected it is not allowed to upload a file with the same name again. If a user should be allowed to upload a file with the same name again this parameter has to be "true". A typical use case would be if the files have different paths.

properties.name: buttonText
properties.description: The Button text can be overwritten using this property.

properties.name: fileType
properties.description: The chosen files will be checked against an array of file types. If at least one file does not fit the file type restriction the upload is prevented. Example: ["jpg", "png", "bmp"].

properties.name: multiple
properties.description: Allows multiple files to be chosen and uploaded from the same folder. This property is not supported by Internet Explorer 9. Note: Keep in mind that the various operating systems for mobile devices can react differently to the property so that fewer upload functions may be available in some cases.

properties.name: maximumFileSize
properties.description: A file size limit in megabytes which prevents the upload if at least one file exceeds it. This property is not supported by Internet Explorer 9.

properties.name: mimeType
properties.description: The chosen files will be checked against an array of mime types. If at least one file does not fit the mime type restriction the upload is prevented. This property is not supported by Internet Explorer 9. Example: mimeType ["image/png", "image/jpeg"].

properties.name: sendXHR
properties.description: If set to "true", the request will be sent as XHR request instead of a form submit. This property is not supported by Internet Explorer 9.

properties.name: placeholder
properties.description: Placeholder for the text field.

properties.name: style
properties.description: Style of the button. "Transparent, "Accept", "Reject", or "Emphasized" is allowed.

properties.name: buttonOnly
properties.description: If set to "true", the FileUploader will be rendered as Button only, without showing the InputField.

properties.name: useMultipart
properties.description: If set to "false", the request will be sent as file only request instead of a multipart/form-data request. Only one file could be uploaded using this type of request. Required for sending such a request is to set the property "sendXHR" to "true". This property is not supported by Internet Explorer 9.

properties.name: maximumFilenameLength
properties.description: The maximum length of a filename which the FileUploader will accept. If the maximum filename length is exceeded, the corresponding Event 'filenameLengthExceed' is fired.

properties.name: valueState
properties.description: Visualizes warnings or errors related to the text field. Possible values: Warning, Error, Success, None.

properties.name: valueStateText
properties.description: Custom text for the value state message pop-up. Note: If not specified, a default text, based on the value state type, will be used instead.

properties.name: icon
properties.description: Icon to be displayed as graphical element within the button. This can be a URI to an image or an icon font URI.

properties.name: iconHovered
properties.description: Icon to be displayed as graphical element within the button when it is hovered (only if also a base icon was specified). If not specified the base icon is used. If an icon font icon is used, this property is ignored.

properties.name: iconSelected
properties.description: Icon to be displayed as graphical element within the button when it is selected (only if also a base icon was specified). If not specified the base or hovered icon is used. If an icon font icon is used, this property is ignored.

properties.name: iconFirst
properties.description: If set to true (default), the display sequence is 1. icon 2. control text.

properties.name: iconOnly
properties.description: If set to true, the button is displayed without any text.

aggregations.name: parameters
aggregations.description: The parameters for the FileUploader which are rendered as a hidden inputfield.

aggregations.name: headerParameters
aggregations.description: The header parameters for the FileUploader which are only submitted with XHR requests. Header parameters are not supported by Internet Explorer 9.

aggregations.name: xhrSettings
aggregations.description: Settings for the XMLHttpRequest object. Note: This aggregation is only used when the sendXHR property is set to true.

events.name: change
events.description: Event is fired when the value of the file path has been changed.

events.name: uploadComplete
events.description: Event is fired as soon as the upload request is completed (either successful or unsuccessful). To see if the upload request was successful, check the 'state' parameter for a value 2xx. The uploads actual progress can be retrieved via the 'uploadProgress' Event. However this covers only the client side of the Upload process and does not give any success status from the server.

fileName.name: fileName
fileName.description: The name of a file to be uploaded.

response.name: response
response.description: Response message which comes from the server. On the server side this response has to be put within the "body" tags of the response document of the iFrame. It can consist of a return code and an optional message. This does not work in cross-domain scenarios.

readyStateXHR.name: readyStateXHR
readyStateXHR.description: ReadyState of the XHR request. Required for receiving a readyState is to set the property "sendXHR" to "true". This property is not supported by Internet Explorer 9.

status.name: status
status.description: Status of the XHR request. Required for receiving a status is to set the property "sendXHR" to "true". This property is not supported by Internet Explorer 9.

responseRaw.name: responseRaw
responseRaw.description: Http-Response which comes from the server. Required for receiving "responseRaw" is to set the property "sendXHR" to true. This property is not supported by Internet Explorer 9.

headers.name: headers
headers.description: Http-Response-Headers which come from the server. provided as a JSON-map, i.e. each header-field is reflected by a property in the header-object, with the property value reflecting the header-field's content. Required for receiving "header" is to set the property "sendXHR" to true. This property is not supported by Internet Explorer 9.

requestHeaders.name: requestHeaders
requestHeaders.description: Http-Request-Headers. Required for receiving "header" is to set the property "sendXHR" to true. This property is not supported by Internet Explorer 9.

events.name: typeMissmatch
events.description: Event is fired when the type of a file does not match the mimeType or fileType property.

fileName.name: fileName
fileName.description: The name of a file to be uploaded.

fileType.name: fileType
fileType.description: The file ending of a file to be uploaded.

mimeType.name: mimeType
mimeType.description: The MIME type of a file to be uploaded.

events.name: fileSizeExceed
events.description: Event is fired when the size of a file is above the maximumFileSize property. This event is not supported by Internet Explorer 9 (same restriction as for the property maximumFileSize).

fileName.name: fileName
fileName.description: The name of a file to be uploaded.

fileSize.name: fileSize
fileSize.description: The size in MB of a file to be uploaded.

events.name: fileAllowed
events.description: Event is fired when the file is allowed for upload on client side.

events.name: uploadProgress
events.description: Event is fired after the upload has started and before the upload is completed and contains progress information related to the running upload. Depending on file size, band width and used browser the event is fired once or multiple times. This is event is only supported with property sendXHR set to true, i.e. the event is not supported in Internet Explorer 9.

lengthComputable.name: lengthComputable
lengthComputable.description: Indicates whether or not the relative upload progress can be calculated out of loaded and total.

loaded.name: loaded
loaded.description: The number of bytes of the file which have been uploaded by to the time the event was fired.

total.name: total
total.description: The total size of the file to be uploaded in byte.

methods.description: Gets current value of property {@link #getButtonOnly buttonOnly}. If set to "true", the FileUploader will be rendered as Button only, without showing the InputField. Default value is false.

methods.description:
Gets current value of property {@link #getButtonText buttonText}.

The Button text can be overwritten using this property.

methods.description: Gets current value of property {@link #getEnabled enabled}. Disabled controls have different colors, depending on customer settings. Default value is true.

methods.name: getFileType

returnValue.description: Value of property fileType

methods.description:
Gets current value of property {@link #getFileType fileType}.

The chosen files will be checked against an array of file types. If at least one file does not fit the file type restriction the upload is prevented. Example: ["jpg", "png", "bmp"].

methods.name: getHeaderParameters
methods.description:
Gets content of aggregation {@link #getHeaderParameters headerParameters}.

The header parameters for the FileUploader which are only submitted with XHR requests. Header parameters are not supported by Internet Explorer 9.

methods.name: getIcon

returnValue.description: Value of property icon

methods.description: Gets current value of property {@link #getIcon icon}. Icon to be displayed as graphical element within the button. This can be a URI to an image or an icon font URI. Default value is empty string.

methods.name: getIconFirst

returnValue.description: Value of property iconFirst

methods.description: Gets current value of property {@link #getIconFirst iconFirst}. If set to true (default), the display sequence is 1. icon 2. control text. Default value is true.

methods.name: getIconHovered

returnValue.description: Value of property iconHovered

methods.description: Gets current value of property {@link #getIconHovered iconHovered}. Icon to be displayed as graphical element within the button when it is hovered (only if also a base icon was specified). If not specified the base icon is used. If an icon font icon is used, this property is ignored. Default value is empty string.

methods.name: getIconOnly

returnValue.description: Value of property iconOnly

methods.description: Gets current value of property {@link #getIconOnly iconOnly}. If set to true, the button is displayed without any text. Default value is false.

methods.name: getIconSelected

returnValue.description: Value of property iconSelected

methods.description: Gets current value of property {@link #getIconSelected iconSelected}. Icon to be displayed as graphical element within the button when it is selected (only if also a base icon was specified). If not specified the base or hovered icon is used. If an icon font icon is used, this property is ignored. Default value is empty string.

returnValue.description: Value of property maximumFilenameLength

methods.description:
Gets current value of property {@link #getMaximumFilenameLength maximumFilenameLength}.

The maximum length of a filename which the FileUploader will accept. If the maximum filename length is exceeded, the corresponding Event 'filenameLengthExceed' is fired.

methods.name: getMaximumFileSize

returnValue.description: Value of property maximumFileSize

methods.description:
Gets current value of property {@link #getMaximumFileSize maximumFileSize}.

A file size limit in megabytes which prevents the upload if at least one file exceeds it. This property is not supported by Internet Explorer 9.

The chosen files will be checked against an array of mime types. If at least one file does not fit the mime type restriction the upload is prevented. This property is not supported by Internet Explorer 9. Example: mimeType ["image/png", "image/jpeg"].

returnValue.description: Value of property multiple

methods.description: Gets current value of property {@link #getMultiple multiple}. Allows multiple files to be chosen and uploaded from the same folder. Placeholder for the text field.

methods.name: getProcessedBlobsFromArray

returnValue.description: A Promise that resolves with an array of Blobs which is used for the final uploading.

parameters.name: aBlobs
parameters.description: The initial Blobs which can be used to determine/calculate a new array of Blobs for further processing.

methods.description: Allows to process Blobs before they get uploaded. This API can be used to create custom Blobs and upload these custom Blobs instead of the received/initials Blobs in the parameter aBlobs. One use case could be to create and upload zip archives based on the passed Blobs. The default implementation of this API should simply resolve with the received Blobs (parameter aBlobs). This API is only supported in case sendXHR is true. This means only IE10+ is supported, while IE9 and below is not. This is a default implementation of the interface sap.ui.unified.IProcessableBlobs.

methods.name: getSameFilenameAllowed

returnValue.description: Value of property sameFilenameAllowed

methods.description: Gets current value of property {@link #getSameFilenameAllowed sameFilenameAllowed}. If the FileUploader is configured to upload the file directly after the file is selected it is not allowed to upload a file with the same name again. If a user should be allowed to upload a file with the same name again this parameter has to be "true". A typical use case would be if the files have different paths. Default value is false.

returnValue.description: Value of property sendXHR

methods.name: getUploadUrl

methods.name: getUseMultipart

Default value is true.

symbols.name: sap.ui.unified.IProcessableBlobs
symbols.description:
Marker interface for controls that process instances of window.Blob, such as window.File. The implementation of this Interface should implement the following Interface methods:
  • getProcessedBlobsFromArray

methods.name: getProcessedBlobsFromArray

returnValue.description: A Promise that resolves with an array of Blobs which is used for the final uploading.

parameters.name: aBlobs
parameters.description: The initial Blobs which can be used to determine a new array of Blobs for further processing.

methods.description: Allows to process Blobs before they get uploaded. This API can be used to create custom Blobs and upload these custom Blobs instead of the received/initials Blobs in the parameter aBlobs. One use case could be to create and upload zip archives based on the passed Blobs. The default implementation of this API should simply resolve with the received Blobs (parameter aBlobs).

symbols.name: sap.ui.unified.Menu
symbols.description: A menu is an interactive element which provides a choice of different actions to the user. These actions (items) can also be organized in submenus. Like other dialog-like controls, the menu is not rendered within the control hierarchy. Instead it can be opened at a specified position via a function call.

properties.name: enabled
properties.description: When a menu is disabled none of its items can be selected by the user. The enabled property of an item (@link sap.ui.unified.MenuItemBase#getEnabled) has no effect when the menu of the item is disabled.

properties.name: ariaDescription
properties.description: Accessible label / description of the menu for assistive technologies like screenreaders.

deprecated.text: replaced by ariaLabelledBy association

properties.name: maxVisibleItems
properties.description: The maximum number of items which are displayed before an overflow mechanism takes effect. A value smaller than 1 means an infinite number of visible items. The overall height of the menu is limited by the height of the screen. If the maximum possible height is reached, an overflow takes effect, even if the maximum number of visible items is not yet reached.

properties.name: pageSize
properties.description: The keyboard can be used to navigate through the items of a menu. Beside the arrow keys for single steps and the Home / End keys for jumping to the first / last item, the Page Up / Page Down keys can be used to jump an arbitrary number of items up or down. This number can be defined via the pageSize property. For values smaller than 1, paging behaves in a similar way to when using the Home / End keys. If the value equals 1, the paging behavior is similar to that of the arrow keys.

aggregations.name: items
aggregations.description: The available actions to be displayed as items of the menu.

symbols.name: sap.ui.unified.Shell
symbols.description: The shell control is meant as root control (full-screen) of an application. It was build as root control of the Fiori Launchpad application and provides the basic capabilities for this purpose. Do not use this control within applications which run inside the Fiori Lauchpad and do not use it for other scenarios than the root control usecase.

properties.name: icon
properties.description: The application icon. If a custom header is set this property has no effect.

properties.name: showCurtain
properties.description: Shows / Hides the curtain.

deprecated.text: Curtain is deprecated and replaced by ShellOverlay mechanism.

properties.name: showCurtainPane
properties.description: Shows / Hides the side pane on the curtain.

deprecated.text: Curtain is deprecated and replaced by ShellOverlay mechanism.

properties.name: searchVisible
properties.description: If set to false, the search area (aggregation 'search') is hidden. If a custom header is set this property has no effect.

aggregations.name: curtainContent
aggregations.description: The content to appear in the curtain area.

aggregations.name: curtainPaneContent
aggregations.description: The content to appear in the pane area of the curtain.

aggregations.name: headItems
aggregations.description: The buttons shown in the begin (left in left-to-right case) of the Shell header. Currently max. 3 visible buttons are supported. If a custom header is set this aggregation has no effect.

aggregations.name: headEndItems
aggregations.description: The buttons shown in the end (right in left-to-right case) of the Shell header. Currently max. 3 visible buttons are supported (when user is set only 1). If a custom header is set this aggregation has no effect.

aggregations.name: search
aggregations.description: Experimental (This aggregation might change in future!): The search control which should be displayed in the shell header. If a custom header is set this aggregation has no effect.

aggregations.name: user
aggregations.description: The user item which is rendered in the shell header beside the items. If a custom header is set this aggregation has no effect.

properties.name: startsSection

deprecated.text: Dividers are not supported anymore.

properties.description: If set to true, a separator is displayed after the item.

properties.name: selected
properties.description: Defines the toggle state in case the item represents a toggle button (see also property toggleEnabled).

properties.name: toggleEnabled
properties.description: If set to true, the item represents a toggle button. The selected property can the be used to define the toggle state. Otherwise the item is displayed as action button. In this case the selected property is ignored.

properties.name: showMarker
properties.description: If set to true, a theme dependent marker is shown on the item.

deprecated.text: Markers should not be used anymore.

properties.name: icon
properties.description: The icon of the item, either defined in the sap.ui.core.IconPool or a URI to a custom image. An icon must be set.

properties.name: visible
properties.description: Invisible items are not shown on the UI.
